  "title": "wt switch + branch resolution: ref-injection, PR fetching, network policy",
  "summary": "`wt switch` resolves user-supplied references (branch names, pr:N, mr:N, gh URLs) and may create worktrees. Branch names can contain hyphens, slashes, special chars — must be passed to git without interpretation as flags. PR/MR fetch is the one place where shelling out to `gh`/`glab` is allowed and must not happen on background paths. See CLAUDE.md > Network Access policy and Worktree Model.",
